  62 @attr.s(slots=True)
  63 class PythonFinder(BaseFinder, BasePath):
  64     root = attr.ib(default=None, validator=optional_instance_of(Path), type=Path)
  65     # should come before versions, because its value is used in versions's default initializer.
  66     #: Whether to ignore any paths which raise exceptions and are not actually python
  67     ignore_unsupported = attr.ib(default=True, type=bool)
  68     #: Glob path for python versions off of the root directory
  69     version_glob_path = attr.ib(default="versions/*", type=str)
  70     #: The function to use to sort version order when returning an ordered verion set
  71     sort_function = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Callable
  72     #: The root locations used for discovery
  73     roots = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(defaultdict), type=defaultdict)
  74     #: List of paths discovered during search
  75     paths = attr.ib(type=list)
  76     #: shim directory
  77     shim_dir = attr.ib(default="shims", type=str)
  78     #: Versions discovered in the specified paths
  79     _versions = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(defaultdict), type=defaultdict)
  80     _pythons = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(defaultdict), type=defaultdict)

 106     def get_version_order(self):
 107         # type: () -> List[Path]
 108         version_paths = [
 109             p
 110             for p in self.root.glob(self.version_glob_path)
 111             if not (p.parent.name == "envs" or p.name == "envs")
 112         ]
 113         versions = {v.name: v for v in version_paths}
 114         version_order = []  # type: List[Path]
 115         if self.is_pyenv:
 116             version_order = [
 117                 versions[v] for v in parse_pyenv_version_order() if v in versions
 118             ]
 119         elif self.is_asdf:
 120             version_order = [
 121                 versions[v] for v in parse_asdf_version_order() if v in versions
 122             ]
 123         for version in version_order:
 124             if version in version_paths:
 125                 version_paths.remove(version)
 126         if version_order:
 127             version_order += version_paths
 128         else:
 129             version_order = version_paths
 130         return version_order
 131 
 132     def get_bin_dir(self, base):
 133         # type: (Union[Path, str]) -> Path
 134         if isinstance(base, six.string_types):
 135             base = Path(base)
 136         return base / "bin"

 138     @classmethod
 139     def version_from_bin_dir(cls, entry):
 140         # type: (PathEntry) -> Optional[PathEntry]
 141         py_version = None
 142         py_version = next(iter(entry.find_all_python_versions()), None)
 143         return py_version

 145     def _iter_version_bases(self):
 146         # type: () -> Iterator[Tuple[Path, PathEntry]]
 147         from .path import PathEntry
 148 
 149         for p in self.get_version_order():
 150             bin_dir = self.get_bin_dir(p)
 151             if bin_dir.exists() and bin_dir.is_dir():
 152                 entry = PathEntry.create(
 153                     path=bin_dir.absolute(), only_python=False, name=p.name, is_root=True
 154                 )
 155                 self.roots[p] = entry
 156                 yield (p, entry)
 157 
 158     def _iter_versions(self):
 159         # type: () -> Iterator[Tuple[Path, PathEntry, Tuple]]
 160         for base_path, entry in self._iter_version_bases():
 161             version = None
 162             version_entry = None
 163             try:
 164                 version = PythonVersion.parse(entry.name)
 165             except (ValueError, InvalidPythonVersion):
 166                 version_entry = next(iter(entry.find_all_python_versions()), None)
 167                 if version is None:
 168                     if not self.ignore_unsupported:
 169                         raise
 170                     continue
 171                 if version_entry is not None:
 172                     version = version_entry.py_version.as_dict()
 173             except Exception:
 174                 if not self.ignore_unsupported:
 175                     raise
 176                 logger.warning(
 177                     "Unsupported Python version %r, ignoring...",
 178                     base_path.name,
 179                     exc_info=True,
 180                 )
 181                 continue
 182             if version is not None:
 183                 version_tuple = (
 184                     version.get("major"),
 185                     version.get("minor"),
 186                     version.get("patch"),
 187                     version.get("is_prerelease"),
 188                     version.get("is_devrelease"),
 189                     version.get("is_debug"),
 190                 )
 191                 yield (base_path, entry, version_tuple)
 192 
 193     @property
 194     def versions(self):
 195         # type: () -> DefaultDict[Tuple, PathEntry]
 196         if not self._versions:
 197             for base_path, entry, version_tuple in self._iter_versions():
 198                 self._versions[version_tuple] = entry
 199         return self._versions
 200 
 201     def _iter_pythons(self):
 202         # type: () -> Iterator
 203         for path, entry, version_tuple in self._iter_versions():
 204             if path.as_posix() in self._pythons:
 205                 yield self._pythons[path.as_posix()]
 206             elif version_tuple not in self.versions:
 207                 for python in entry.find_all_python_versions():
 208                     yield python
 209             else:
 210                 yield self.versions[version_tuple]
 211 
 212     @paths.default
 213     def get_paths(self):
 214         # type: () -> List[PathEntry]
 215         _paths = [base for _, base in self._iter_version_bases()]
 216         return _paths

 254     def find_all_python_versions(
 255         self,
 256         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 257         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 258         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 259         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 260         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 261         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 262         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 263     ):
 264         # type: (...) -> List[PathEntry]
 265         """Search for a specific python version on the path. Return all copies
 266 
 267         :param major: Major python version to search for.
 268         :type major: int
 269         :param int minor: Minor python version to search for, defaults to None
 270         :param int patch: Patch python version to search for, defaults to None
 271         :param bool pre: Search for prereleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 272         :param bool dev: Search for devreleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 273         :param str arch: Architecture to include, e.g. '64bit', defaults to None
 274         :param str name: The name of a python version, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 275         :return: A list of :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instances matching the version requested.
 276         :rtype: List[:class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry`]
 277         """
 278 
 279         call_method = "find_all_python_versions" if self.is_dir else "find_python_version"
 280         sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 281             call_method, major, minor, patch, pre, dev, arch, name
 282         )
 283         if not any([major, minor, patch, name]):
 284             pythons = [
 285                 next(iter(py for py in base.find_all_python_versions()), None)
 286                 for _, base in self._iter_version_bases()
 287             ]
 288         else:
 289             pythons = [sub_finder(path) for path in self.paths]
 290         pythons = expand_paths(pythons, True)
 291         version_sort = operator.attrgetter("as_python.version_sort")
 292         paths = [
 293             p for p in sorted(pythons, key=version_sort, reverse=True) if p is not None
 294         ]
 295         return paths
 296 
 297     def find_python_version(
 298         self,
 299         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 300         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 301         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 302         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 303         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 304         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 305         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 306     ):
 307         # type: (...) -> Optional[PathEntry]
 308         """Search or self for the specified Python version and return the first match.
 309 
 310         :param major: Major version number.
 311         :type major: int
 312         :param int minor: Minor python version to search for, defaults to None
 313         :param int patch: Patch python version to search for, defaults to None
 314         :param bool pre: Search for prereleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 315         :param bool dev: Search for devreleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 316         :param str arch: Architecture to include, e.g. '64bit', defaults to None
 317         :param str name: The name of a python version, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 318         :returns: A :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instance matching the version requested.
 319         """
 320 
 321         sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 322             "find_python_version", major, minor, patch, pre, dev, arch, name
 323         )
 324         version_sort = operator.attrgetter("as_python.version_sort")
 325         unnested = [sub_finder(self.roots[path]) for path in self.roots]
 326         unnested = [
 327             p
 328             for p in unnested
 329             if p is not None and p.is_python and p.as_python is not None
 330         ]
 331         paths = sorted(list(unnested), key=version_sort, reverse=True)
 332         return next(iter(p for p in paths if p is not None), None)
 333 
 334     def which(self, name):
 335         # type: (str) -> Optional[PathEntry]
 336         """Search in this path for an executable.
 337 
 338         :param executable: The name of an executable to search for.
 339         :type executable: str
 340         :returns: :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instance.
 341         """
 342 
 343         matches = (p.which(name) for p in self.paths)
 344         non_empty_match = next(iter(m for m in matches if m is not None), None)
 345         return non_empty_match

 348 @attr.s(slots=True)
 349 class PythonVersion(object):
 350     major = attr.ib(default=0, type=int)
 351     minor = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[int]
 352     patch = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[int]
 353     is_prerelease = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
 354     is_postrelease = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
 355     is_devrelease = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
 356     is_debug = attr.ib(default=False, type=bool)
 357     version = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Version
 358     architecture = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[str]
 359     comes_from = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[PathEntry]
 360     executable = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[str]
 361     company = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[str]
 362     name = attr.ib(default=None, type=str)
 363 
 364     def __getattribute__(self, key):
 365         result = super(PythonVersion, self).__getattribute__(key)
 366         if key in ["minor", "patch"] and result is None:
 367             executable = None  # type: Optional[str]
 368             if self.executable:
 369                 executable = self.executable
 370             elif self.comes_from:
 371                 executable = self.comes_from.path.as_posix()
 372             if executable is not None:
 373                 if not isinstance(executable, six.string_types):
 374                     executable = executable.as_posix()
 375                 instance_dict = self.parse_executable(executable)
 376                 for k in instance_dict.keys():
 377                     try:
 378                         super(PythonVersion, self).__getattribute__(k)
 379                     except AttributeError:
 380                         continue
 381                     else:
 382                         setattr(self, k, instance_dict[k])
 383                 result = instance_dict.get(key)
 384         return result
 385 
 386     @property
 387     def version_sort(self):
 388         # type: () -> Tuple[int, int, Optional[int], int, int]
 389         """
 390         A tuple for sorting against other instances of the same class.
 391 
 392         Returns a tuple of the python version but includes points for core python,
 393         non-dev,  and non-prerelease versions.  So released versions will have 2 points
 394         for this value.  E.g. ``(1, 3, 6, 6, 2)`` is a release, ``(1, 3, 6, 6, 1)`` is a
 395         prerelease, ``(1, 3, 6, 6, 0)`` is a dev release, and ``(1, 3, 6, 6, 3)`` is a
 396         postrelease.  ``(0, 3, 7, 3, 2)`` represents a non-core python release, e.g. by
 397         a repackager of python like Continuum.
 398         """
 399         company_sort = 1 if (self.company and self.company == "PythonCore") else 0
 400         release_sort = 2
 401         if self.is_postrelease:
 402             release_sort = 3
 403         elif self.is_prerelease:
 404             release_sort = 1
 405         elif self.is_devrelease:
 406             release_sort = 0
 407         elif self.is_debug:
 408             release_sort = 1
 409         return (
 410             company_sort,
 411             self.major,
 412             self.minor,
 413             self.patch if self.patch else 0,
 414             release_sort,
 415         )
 416 
 417     @property
 418     def version_tuple(self):
 419         # type: () -> Tuple[int, Optional[int], Optional[int], bool, bool, bool]
 420         """
 421         Provides a version tuple for using as a dictionary key.
 422 
 423         :return: A tuple describing the python version meetadata contained.
 424         :rtype: tuple
 425         """
 426 
 427         return (
 428             self.major,
 429             self.minor,
 430             self.patch,
 431             self.is_prerelease,
 432             self.is_devrelease,
 433             self.is_debug,
 434         )

 436     def matches(
 437         self,
 438         major=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 439         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 440         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 441         pre=False,  # type: bool
 442         dev=False,  # type: bool
 443         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 444         debug=False,  # type: bool
 445         python_name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 446     ):
 447         # type: (...) -> bool
 448         result = False
 449         if arch:
 450             own_arch = self.get_architecture()
 451             if arch.isdigit():
 452                 arch = "{0}bit".format(arch)
 453         if (
 454             (major is None or self.major and self.major == major)
 455             and (minor is None or self.minor and self.minor == minor)
 456             and (patch is None or self.patch and self.patch == patch)
 457             and (pre is None or self.is_prerelease == pre)
 458             and (dev is None or self.is_devrelease == dev)
 459             and (arch is None or own_arch == arch)
 460             and (debug is None or self.is_debug == debug)
 461             and (
 462                 python_name is None
 463                 or (python_name and self.name)
 464                 and (self.name == python_name or self.name.startswith(python_name))
 465             )
 466         ):
 467             result = True
 468         return result

 496     def update_metadata(self, metadata):
 497         # type: (Dict[str, Union[str, int, Version]]) -> None
 498         """
 499         Update the metadata on the current :class:`pythonfinder.models.python.PythonVersion`
 500 
 501         Given a parsed version dictionary from :func:`pythonfinder.utils.parse_python_version`,
 502         update the instance variables of the current version instance to reflect the newly
 503         supplied values.
 504         """
 505 
 506         for key in metadata:
 507             try:
 508                 _ = getattr(self, key)
 509             except AttributeError:
 510                 continue
 511             else:
 512                 setattr(self, key, metadata[key])

 514     @classmethod
 515     @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 516     def parse(cls, version):
 517         # type: (str) -> Dict[str, Union[str, int, Version]]
 518         """
 519         Parse a valid version string into a dictionary
 520 
 521         Raises:
 522             ValueError -- Unable to parse version string
 523             ValueError -- Not a valid python version
 524             TypeError -- NoneType or unparseable type passed in
 525 
 526         :param str version: A valid version string
 527         :return: A dictionary with metadata about the specified python version.
 528         :rtype: dict
 529         """
 530 
 531         if version is None:
 532             raise TypeError("Must pass a value to parse!")
 533         version_dict = parse_python_version(str(version))
 534         if not version_dict:
 535             raise ValueError("Not a valid python version: %r" % version)
 536         return version_dict
 537 
 538     def get_architecture(self):
 539         # type: () -> str
 540         if self.architecture:
 541             return self.architecture
 542         arch = None
 543         if self.comes_from is not None:
 544             arch, _ = platform.architecture(self.comes_from.path.as_posix())
 545         elif self.executable is not None:
 546             arch, _ = platform.architecture(self.executable)
 547         if arch is None:
 548             arch, _ = platform.architecture(sys.executable)
 549         self.architecture = arch
 550         return self.architecture
 551 
 552     @classmethod
 553     def from_path(cls, path, name=None, ignore_unsupported=True, company=None):
 554         # type: (Union[str, PathEntry], Optional[str], bool, Optional[str]) -> PythonVersion
 555         """
 556         Parses a python version from a system path.
 557 
 558         Raises:
 559             ValueError -- Not a valid python path
 560 
 561         :param path: A string or :class:`~pythonfinder.models.path.PathEntry`
 562         :type path: str or :class:`~pythonfinder.models.path.PathEntry` instance
 563         :param str name: Name of the python distribution in question
 564         :param bool ignore_unsupported: Whether to ignore or error on unsupported paths.
 565         :param Optional[str] company: The company or vendor packaging the distribution.
 566         :return: An instance of a PythonVersion.
 567         :rtype: :class:`~pythonfinder.models.python.PythonVersion`
 568         """
 569 
 570         from .path import PathEntry
 571 
 572         if not isinstance(path, PathEntry):
 573             path = PathEntry.create(path, is_root=False, only_python=True, name=name)
 574         from ..environment import IGNORE_UNSUPPORTED
 575 
 576         ignore_unsupported = ignore_unsupported or IGNORE_UNSUPPORTED
 577         path_name = getattr(path, "name", path.path.name)  # str
 578         if not path.is_python:
 579             if not (ignore_unsupported or IGNORE_UNSUPPORTED):
 580                 raise ValueError("Not a valid python path: %s" % path.path)
 581         try:
 582             instance_dict = cls.parse(path_name)
 583         except Exception:
 584             instance_dict = cls.parse_executable(path.path.absolute().as_posix())
 585         else:
 586             if instance_dict.get("minor") is None and looks_like_python(path.path.name):
 587                 instance_dict = cls.parse_executable(path.path.absolute().as_posix())
 588 
 589         if (
 590             not isinstance(instance_dict.get("version"), Version)
 591             and not ignore_unsupported
 592         ):
 593             raise ValueError("Not a valid python path: %s" % path)
 594         if instance_dict.get("patch") is None:
 595             instance_dict = cls.parse_executable(path.path.absolute().as_posix())
 596         if name is None:
 597             name = path_name
 598         if company is None:
 599             company = guess_company(path.path.as_posix())
 600         instance_dict.update(
 601             {"comes_from": path, "name": name, "executable": path.path.as_posix()}
 602         )
 603         return cls(**instance_dict)  # type: ignore
 604 
 605     @classmethod
 606     @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 607     def parse_executable(cls, path):
 608         # type: (str) -> Dict[str, Optional[Union[str, int, Version]]]
 609         result_dict = {}  # type: Dict[str, Optional[Union[str, int, Version]]]
 610         result_version = None  # type: Optional[str]
 611         if path is None:
 612             raise TypeError("Must pass a valid path to parse.")
 613         if not isinstance(path, six.string_types):
 614             path = path.as_posix()
 615         # if not looks_like_python(path):
 616         #     raise ValueError("Path %r does not look like a valid python path" % path)
 617         try:
 618             result_version = get_python_version(path)
 619         except Exception:
 620             raise ValueError("Not a valid python path: %r" % path)
 621         if result_version is None:
 622             raise ValueError("Not a valid python path: %s" % path)
 623         result_dict = cls.parse(result_version.strip())
 624         return result_dict
 625 
 626     @classmethod
 627     def from_windows_launcher(cls, launcher_entry, name=None, company=None):
 628         # type: (Environment, Optional[str], Optional[str]) -> PythonVersion
 629         """Create a new PythonVersion instance from a Windows Launcher Entry
 630 
 631         :param launcher_entry: A python launcher environment object.
 632         :param Optional[str] name: The name of the distribution.
 633         :param Optional[str] company: The name of the distributing company.
 634         :return: An instance of a PythonVersion.
 635         :rtype: :class:`~pythonfinder.models.python.PythonVersion`
 636         """
 637 
 638         from .path import PathEntry
 639 
 640         creation_dict = cls.parse(launcher_entry.info.version)
 641         base_path = ensure_path(launcher_entry.info.install_path.__getattr__(""))
 642         default_path = base_path / "python.exe"
 643         if not default_path.exists():
 644             default_path = base_path / "Scripts" / "python.exe"
 645         exe_path = ensure_path(
 646             getattr(launcher_entry.info.install_path, "executable_path", default_path)
 647         )
 648         company = getattr(launcher_entry, "company", guess_company(exe_path.as_posix()))
 649         creation_dict.update(
 650             {
 651                 "architecture": getattr(
 652                     launcher_entry.info, "sys_architecture", SYSTEM_ARCH
 653                 ),
 654                 "executable": exe_path,
 655                 "name": name,
 656                 "company": company,
 657             }
 658         )
 659         py_version = cls.create(**creation_dict)
 660         comes_from = PathEntry.create(exe_path, only_python=True, name=name)
 661         py_version.comes_from = comes_from
 662         py_version.name = comes_from.name
 663         return py_version
 664 
 665     @classmethod
 666     def create(cls, **kwargs):
 667         # type: (...) -> PythonVersion
 668         if "architecture" in kwargs:
 669             if kwargs["architecture"].isdigit():
 670                 kwargs["architecture"] = "{0}bit".format(kwargs["architecture"])
 671         return cls(**kwargs)

 673 
 674 @attr.s
 675 class VersionMap(object):
 676     versions = attr.ib(
 677         factory=defaultdict
 678     )  # type: DefaultDict[Tuple[int, Optional[int], Optional[int], bool, bool, bool], List[PathEntry]]
 679 
 680     def add_entry(self, entry):
 681         # type: (...) -> None
 682         version = entry.as_python  # type: PythonVersion
 683         if version:
 684             _ = self.versions[version.version_tuple]
 685             paths = {p.path for p in self.versions.get(version.version_tuple, [])}
 686             if entry.path not in paths:
 687                 self.versions[version.version_tuple].append(entry)
 688 
 689     def merge(self, target):
 690         # type: (VersionMap) -> None
 691         for version, entries in target.versions.items():
 692             if version not in self.versions:
 693                 self.versions[version] = entries
 694             else:
 695                 current_entries = {
 696                     p.path
 697                     for p in self.versions[version]  # type: ignore
 698                     if version in self.versions
 699                 }
 700                 new_entries = {p.path for p in entries}
 701                 new_entries -= current_entries
 702                 self.versions[version].extend(
 703                     [e for e in entries if e.path in new_entries]
 704                 )
